# Crazy Crane

## Repository
https://github.com/AmazingSteven14/ANGM-2305-Final_Project.git

## Description
## My project is going to be an interactive game that involves elements of a crane claw game you would see in an arcade. It relates to digital art and media since it involves using code to make the art of the game and functions too.
## Features
- Feature 1
	- The crane is going to be moving back and forth inside the claw machine by probably using range in order to determine where it is moving.
- Feature 2
	- The items that are on the bottom of the machine are going to be moving around as well to make it more difficult.
- Feature 3
	- The user will be able to left click on the screen in order to drop the crane claw down and try to catch the items

## Challenges
- Will have to learn more about coding the movement of objects and range as well
- Research more about the pygame draw library to draw the objects and crane of the game
- Learn more about how to make everything function right together with different objects

## Outcomes
Ideal Outcome:
- Having a fully functional crane game where the objects and crane move back and forth, drawings of the crane and objects made, and different levels of difficulty to choose from.

Minimal Viable Outcome:
- Have a functional game where the crane can move and there is at least one object in the game to pick up.

